      "side": 1,
      "message": "[minor] Line 153: 🟡 The `setCurrentCameraZoom` call is made from the UI thread inside a `ValueAnimator` update listener, but `setZoomRatio` in `CameraService` posts work to a camera handler thread and returns the clamped value synchronously based on stored state. This is fine for correctness, but the throttling logic (`abs(v - lastApplied) \u003e\u003d 0.05f`) uses float equality check `v \u003d\u003d end` which may never be exactly true due to floating-point rounding in the animator. Consider using `\u003e\u003d end - epsilon` instead:\n```suggestion\n                if (kotlin.math.abs(v - lastApplied) \u003e\u003d 0.05f || v \u003e\u003d end - 0.001f) {\n```",
      "revId": "43a0949874ea6086ed6b0a601e3a3ebe1dff2044",
