      "message": "[minor] Line 64: 🟡 `setPinchToZoomEnabled` can be called from `ParticipantsContainerView` during layout updates. When toggling from enabled→disabled, the zoom helper\u0027s internal state (scale/translate) is lost but the view\u0027s transform is reset via `configureTransform`. However, when re-enabling later, a new `VideoDisplayZoomHelper` is created without resetting the `TextureView` transform first. If `configureTransform` is called with ratioWidth/ratioHeight \u003d\u003d 0 (before first frame), the identity matrix is set, which could flash an incorrectly-scaled frame. Consider guarding with `if (ratioWidth \u003e 0 \u0026\u0026 ratioHeight \u003e 0)`.",
